
# Https vs gRPC

# Https is a protocol that is used to send data over the internet. It is a request-response protocol. It is a stateless protocol. It is a text-based protocol. It is a synchronous protocol. It is a connectionless protocol. It is a client-server protocol.

# gRPC is a protocol that is used to send data over the internet. It is a request-response protocol. It is a stateful protocol. It is a binary-based protocol. It is an asynchronous protocol. It is a connection-oriented protocol. It is a peer-to-peer protocol. It is a service-oriented protocol. It is a framework. It is a remote procedure call protocol. 